1.title: It's Contagious

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Chris and Sean meet Barney, who they haven't seen in years. Apparently he is married and has a child now. To Chris and Sean's surprise Barney is not the only one of their old friends who moved on with it's life.

2.title: The Perfect Son

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: Chris' parents come to visit, which makes Chris nervous. Sean on the other hand looks forward to his friend having a hard time.

3.title: This Is Ridiculous

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Chris and Sean meet their friends Marcus, Tiffany, Courtney and Jake for a nice camping trip in the woods. But the trip turns out not to be as fun as they expected.

4.title: We're Going to Be Rich

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: As always Chris and Sean got bored again, but they have a great idea. They are going to buy a bar, or start a band or ....

5.title: Oldies

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: When Chris and Sean go to their favorite pub, they notice that music has changed. Nowadays everything sounds like a cat in distress.

6.title: Sleep All Day, Party All Night

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: The gang is back together, joking around and having a good time. Only Chris isn't really paying attention to his friends, he has his eye set on someone else.

7.title: Have You Tried Turning It Off and on Again?

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: Sean visits his parents back home. His dad is pretty relaxed as always, but his mother bombards him with questions and requests... as always.

8.title: Not Enough Experience

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: Because of his new girlfriend, Emily, Chris wants to get a job to better himself. Sean doesn't really agree with Chris' recent behavior.

9.title: ...aches

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

9.plot: After a wild night of drinking, Chris and Sean feel the consequences the next morning.

10.title: Wonderful Learning Opportunity

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

10.plot: Chris and Sean finally managed to get a job. They start their new path full op hope and enthusiasm, but it is short-lived.

11.title: Reckless Behaviour

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

11.plot: On a slow day, Chris and Sean are talking about what the future has in store for them. But an annoying stranger keeps bothering them. Chris would just ignore her, but Sean isn't that level-headed.

12.title: White Picket Fence

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

12.plot: Chris and Emily finally take the first big step and are looking for a place together. They start off with much enthusiasm, but their bubble gets burst soon enough.

13.title: IYKWIM

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

13.plot: Chris and Sean took Emily and Tess on a nice double date picnic in the park. All is well and they have a great time, but some annoying teenagers arrive and are being... annoying. Plus they don't really care about the couples' nice day.

14.title: We Have Plans?

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

14.plot: The gang is back together for Donald and Fiona's wedding and are catching up on each others lives.

15.title: Goodbye for Now

episode of.title: Why Life Sucks When You're in Your 20s (TV Series 2016– )

15.plot: The season finale: Chris and Sean suffer the consequences for their actions at the wedding reception.

imdb.plot outline: Chris and Sean are 2 friends, sharing a flat and trying to find their place in life. They encounter all kinds of recognizable situations like technology taking over, people without consideration for others, losing personal connection with your friends, etc... They try their best to stay the same, stay young. But eventually everybody has to grow up.
